Porto Defeats Braga 1-0 in All-Portuguese Europa League Soccer Final

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-05-18T20:39:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/porto-defeats-braga-1-0-in-all-portuguese-europa-league-soccer-final.html
Porto beat Portuguese rival Braga 1-0
in the final of soccer’s Europa League in Dublin.  Radamel Falcao scored in the final minute of the first half
at the Dublin Arena as Porto won  Europe ’s second-tier club
competition for a second time. It was his 17th goal of the
tournament, extending his single-season record.  Porto previously won the competition in 2003 when it was
known as the UEFA Cup, while Braga was playing in the final for
the first time. Porto has also won the league title and will
play for a third trophy in the Portuguese Cup final in four
days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  